1. What is the difference between Error and Exception? Explain with examples
Error : 
Error is a serious problem that occurs at system level and usually cannot be handled by the program.
Example : 
public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        main(args);   
    }
}
This program throw java.lang.StackOverflowError.

Exception :
An Exception is a problem that occurs during program execution but can be handled using try-catch.
Example : 
public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            int a = 10;
            int b = 0;
            int result = a / b;
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            System.out.println("Cannot divide by zero!");
        }
    }
}
Output : 
Cannot divide by zero!


2. Write a program for handling exception
package Java;

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Exceptionhandling{
	public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        try {
            System.out.println("Enter first number:");
            int num1 = sc.nextInt();

            System.out.println("Enter second number:");
            int num2 = sc.nextInt();

            int result = num1 / num2;   
            System.out.println("Result = " + result);
        }
        catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            System.out.println("Error: Cannot divide by zero!");
        }
        catch (Exception e) {
            System.out.println("Invalid input!");
        }
        finally {
            System.out.println("Program executed successfully.");
        }

        sc.close();
    }

}
